\c 8
\cl 1 Paralipomenon 8
\cd The posterity of Benjamin is further declared down to Saul. His issue.
\p
\v 1 Now *Benjamin begot Bale, his first-born, Asbel, the second, Ahara, the third,
\p
\v 2 Nohaa, the fourth, and Rapha, the fifth.
\p
\v 3 And the sons of Bale were: Addar, and Gera, and Abiud,
\p
\v 4 And Abisue, and Naaman, and Ahoe,
\p
\v 5 And Gera, and Sephuphan, and Huram.
\p
\v 6 These are the sons of Ahod, heads of families that dwelt in Gabaa, who were removed into Manahath.
\p
\v 7 And Naaman, and Achia, and Gera, he removed them, and begot Oza, and Ahiud.
\p
\v 8 And Saharim begot in the land of Moab, after he sent away Husim and Bara, his wives.
\p
\v 9 And he begot of Hodes, his wife, Jobab, and Sebia, and Mosa, and Molchom,
\p
\v 10 And Jehus, and Sechia, and Marma. These were his sons, heads of their families.
\p
\v 11 And Mehusim begot Abitob, and Elphaal.
\p
\v 12 And the sons of Elphaal: were Heber, and Misaam, and Samad: who built Ono, and Lod, and its daughters.
\p
\v 13 And Baria, and Sama, were heads of their kindreds that dwelt in Aialon: these drove away the inhabitants of Geth.
\p
\v 14 And Ahio, and Sesac, and Jerimoth,
\p
\v 15 And Zabadia, and Arod, and Heder,
\p
\v 16 And Michael, and Jespha, and Joha, the sons of Baria,
\p
\v 17 And Zabadia, and Mosollam, and Hezeci, and Heber,
\p
\v 18 And Jesamari, and Jezlia, and Jobab, sons of Elphaal,
\p
\v 19 And Jacim, and Zechri, and Zabdi,
\p
\v 20 And Elioenai, and Selethai, and Elial,
\p
\v 21 And Adaia, and Baraia, and Samareth, the sons of Semei.
\p
\v 22 And Jespham, and Heber, and Eliel,
\p
\v 23 And Abdon, and Zechri, and Hanan,
\p
\v 24 And Hanania, and Elam, and Anathothia,
\p
\v 25 And Jephdaia, and Phanuel the sons of Sesac.
\p
\v 26 And Samsari, and Sohoria, and Otholia,
\p
\v 27 And Jersia, and Alia, and Zechri, the sons of Jeroham.
\p
\v 28 These were the chief fathers, and heads of their families, who dwelt in Jerusalem.
\p
\v 29 And *at Gabaon dwelt Abigabaon, and the name of his wife was Maacha:
\p
\v 30 And his first-born son Abdon, and Sur, and Cis, and Baal, and Nadab,
\p
\v 31 And Gedor, and Ahio, and Zacher, and Macelloth.
\p
\v 32 And Macelloth begot Samaa: and they dwelt over-against their brethren in Jerusalem, with their brethren.
\p
\v 33 *And Ner begot Cis, and Cis begot Saul. And Saul begot Jonathan and Melchisua, and Abinadab, and Esbaal.
\p
\v 34 And the son of Jonathan was Meribbaal: and Meribbaal begot Micha.
\p
\v 35 And the sons of Micha, were Phithon, and Melech, and Tharaa, and Ahaz.
\p
\v 36 And Ahaz begot Joada: and Joada begot Alamath, and Azmoth, and Zamri: and Zamri begot Mosa,
\p
\v 37 And Mosa begot Banaa, whose son was Rapha, of whom was born Elasa, who begot Asel.
\p
\v 38 And Asel had six sons, whose names were Ezricam, Bochru, Ismahel, Saria, Obdia, and Hanan. All these were the sons of Asel.
\p
\v 39 And the sons of Esec, his brother, were Ulam, the first-born, and Jehus, the second, and Eliphalet, the third.
\p
\v 40 And the sons of Ulam were most valiant men, and archers of great strength: and they had many sons and grandsons, even to a hundred and fifty. All these were children of Benjamin.
